## Sub-agent Routing

| Task | Agent |
|---|---|
| Architecture, planning | `architect` (opus) |
| Implementation | `implementer`<% if (implementerVariant !== 'generic') { %> (<%= implementerVariant %> variant)<% } %> (sonnet) |
| Code review (after every implementation session) | `code-reviewer` (sonnet) |
<% if (hasSecurityReviewer) { -%>
| Security review (parallel to code review) | `security-reviewer` (sonnet) |
<% } -%>
| Review loop orchestration (post-task) | `reviewer` (haiku) |
| Optimization pass | `code-optimizer` (sonnet) |
| Unit tests | `test-writer` (haiku) |
<% if (hasE2eTester) { -%>
| E2E tests | `e2e-tester` (haiku) |
<% } -%>
<% if (hasUiDesigner) { -%>
| UI/UX design & review | `ui-designer` (opus) |
<% } -%>

**Model tiering rationale.** Deep-reasoning roles (`architect`<% if (hasUiDesigner) { %>, `ui-designer`<% } %>) → opus. Code-judgement roles (`implementer`, `code-reviewer`<% if (hasSecurityReviewer) { %>, `security-reviewer`<% } %>, `code-optimizer`) → sonnet. Rule-following roles (`reviewer` orchestrator, `test-writer`<% if (hasE2eTester) { %>, `e2e-tester`<% } %>) → **haiku** — cuts token cost ~3-5× per call without hurting quality, since the high-judgement agents they invoke still run on sonnet.

Use sub-agents with independent, single, simple tasks as much as possible.
<% if (hasUiDesigner) { -%>

**Mandatory ui-designer routing:** every UI/UX implementation must go through the `ui-designer` sub-agent *before* any implementation agent writes code.
<% } -%>

